    "body": "Does anyone have a solution to this problem ?\r\nWe are using Geth1.7.3-stable-4bb3c89d ver, we have configured two PoA nodes with two signer accounts one on each node. Both the signers must sign a transaction to store it in Blockchain. \r\n\r\nThe problem i am facing is with the miners are stopped when geth instances are started, \r\n**WARN [01-22|19:07:12] Block sealing failed                     err=\"authentication needed: password or unlock\"** \r\n\r\nEven if i am trying to unlock the accounts \r\npersonal.unlockAccount(eth.coinbase.....) -> return true\r\nminer.start() -> return null \r\nMiners are not started.\r\n\r\nSometimes personal.unlockAccount(eth.coinbase.....) command is killing the Geth instance.\r\n\r\nCould this be a problem with memory ?\r\n\r\nOr any suggestion is highly appreciated.\r\n",
